\subsubsection{Data preparation}

In the first instance we performed data quality control on the district-level inventory dataset to remove noise from the time series data. The main data quality problems we encountered in the dataset were time series labelled as one crop type but actually belonging to another, data points labelled with the wrong area units, outliers and missing data points. These were identified by plotting the time series data of each crop type under consideration for each district unit. Mislabelled time series, to the extent that they could be identified, were changed to the correct crop type. Where possible missing data points were infilled using the ICRISAT dataset; otherwise they were infilled using a combination of linear interpolation or, if data points were missing from the start or end of the time series, last observation carried forwards. Outliers were removed and treated as missing data points. In States or Union Territories with consistently poor data availability at the district level we used state level data from Agricultural Censuses. \\

